tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  22,49,"He fails to differentiate between the world of trial and the world of reward."
  22,54,"All this is in order to ensure that man should live in this world with humility and modesty. But the transgressor does not learn any lesson from any of these things. He does not come to his senses until he loses everything and only after being deprived of everything does he come to realise—after seeing it with his own eyes— that he possessed nothing but total helplessness."